{"TRAJECT":[{"def":"To throw or cast through, over, or across; as, to traject the sun's light through three or more cross prisms.","pos":""}],"TRAJECTION":[{"def":"The act of trajecting; a throwing or casting through or across; also, emission.","pos":""}],"TRAJECTORY":[{"def":"The curve which a body describes in space, as a planet or comet in its orbit, or stone thrown upward obliquely in the air.","pos":""},{"def":"See Treget, Tregetour, and Tregetry.","pos":""}]}